article.headline: Illinois St. 64, Miami (Ohio) 40
article.story: NORMAL, Ill. (AP) -- Anthony Slack scored 15 points and pulled down 10 rebounds to lead Illinois State in a 64-40 win over Miami of Ohio on Tuesday night. Boo Richardson added 13 points for the Redbirds (6-2), while Greg Dilligard scored 11 and added 10 rebounds of his own. Slack was 7-for-10 from the foul line. Tim Pollitz had 17 points for Miami of Ohio (3-5) to lead all scorers and Nathan Peavy chipped in 10 points before fouling out with 3:31 to go in the game. The RedHawks led 27-25 at halftime, but shot just 6-for-26 (23 percent) after the break while Illinois State went 13-for-25 (52 percent). It was the sixth straight win for the Redbirds after opening the season with two losses.
